      {
        "title": "Authors With URLs Demo",
        "publisher": "Manual Test",
        "primary": true
      }
    ],
    "authors": [
      "Plain Author",
      {
        "name": "Author With A Valid Link",
        "url": "https://example.com/author-with-a-valid-link"
      },
      {
        "name": "Author With A Bad Link",
        "url": "not-a-valid-url"
      },
      "Foo Bar, Jr."
    ],
    "description": "The `authors` list below mixes every case #95's viewer/editor guard need to tell apart ([[field-schema#authors]]): a plain name; a record with a strict http/https `url`, rendering a trailing `(url)` link in the viewer (hover it for the tooltip/status-tip, click to open); a record whose `url` doesn't parse as http/https, rendering as a plain name with no link at all; and a plain name containing a comma, which the comma editor can't losslessly round-trip. Because the list carries a record entry and a comma-bearing name, the Main Editor's `authors` field should show read-only with an explanatory tooltip rather than the usual editable line."
  },
  "tutorial": {
    "format_version": 0,
    "rating": 4,
    "complete": true
  }
}
